text:
It’s been a decade since Drake left Degrassi: The Next Generation to pursue a career in music, but he’s still earning royalties from the show. The 30-year-old Toronto native took to Instagram on Tuesday to share a photo of a check for $8.25. “Degrassi money still coming in don’t sleeeeeeeep…“ he jokingly captioned the shot. Drake, who is currently worth an estimated $90 million, starred on Degrassi for eight consecutive seasons between 2001-2007 as a star basketball player who became paralyzed after a classmate shot him during the series’ well-known school shooting episode.
